<DocsLayout title="Hosting a world" description="Share your singleplayer world over the mesh.">
  <p>Open a singleplayer world, then host it:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Open the menu (<span class="kbd">G</span>) → <strong>Host this world</strong>.</li>
    <li>Enter a <strong>network name</strong> and optional <strong>secret</strong> (peers must match both).</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Start hosting</strong>.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>What happens</h2>
  <p>etmc:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>starts an EasyTier instance (no-TUN) with a fixed virtual IP <code>10.126.126.1</code>;</li>
    <li>runs Minecraft's <em>Open to LAN</em> on a loopback port;</li>
    <li>forwards each peer that connects over the mesh to that local port.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Invite</h2>
  <p>
    A <strong>join code</strong> (<code>ETMC1:…</code>) is generated containing the network name, secret, relays and
    host address. Share it in chat. <code>/etmc invite</code> copies it to your clipboard at any time.
  </p>

  <div class="note">Keep the world open while friends are connected — leaving stops the mesh instance.</div>
</DocsLayout>
